// 3.835 — Sitemap completeness fix — added /careers (weekly, 0.6), /terms-of-use (yearly, 0.3), and /health-data-policy (yearly, 0.3) to sitemap.ts. Pre-fix all three pages had full metadata + canonical + default index/follow but were missing from sitemap.ts, so search engines couldn't discover them via the canonical sitemap discovery path. /careers especially is a real SEO gap — it's the public job listing surface that captures "Wenatchee cannabis jobs" / "dispensary hiring near me" search traffic. Added explicit-exclusion comments for /alumni (was already there) and /apply (form, no canonical). Mirror on seattle-cannabis-web v4.585. tsc clean.
// 3.825 — Brand-voice "may" hedge sweep — 3 customer-facing surfaces. (1) `/alumni` knock-form post-submit panel: "your browser may have blocked it" → "your browser blocked it" (when this fallback shows, the mailto: action factually didn't open — the hedge masked a confident statement). (2+3) Boutique brand pages 2k-gardens.tsx + avitas.tsx: "refresh tomorrow, the mix may have rotated" → "refresh tomorrow, the mix often rotates" (factual confident framing — the mix DOES rotate often, that's the point). Per brand-voice doc § "What we never do" line 204: "Hedge. No 'may', 'might', 'we believe' in customer-facing UI. Either it's true or it's not." Mirror on seattle-cannabis-web v4.575 (same 2 brand pages; no /alumni equivalent on Seattle). tsc clean.
