// 3.745 — Sativa color: amber → red across all 7 customer-facing surfaces. Catches the public sites up to the strain-color convention update Doug landed today (memory `reference_strain_type_color_convention`: Indica=purple, Sativa=red, Hybrid=green/emerald — previous orange/teal swapped to red/green). Inventoryapp shipped this earlier (changelog "Strain colors corrected. Sativa → red, Hybrid → green, Indica → purple"); public sites were behind. Surfaces fixed: `app/order/OrderMenu.tsx` strain badge + dot · `app/brands/[slug]/page.tsx` strain badge · `app/brands/[slug]/_brands/PaginatedProductsGrid.tsx` strain badge · `app/deals/[id]/page.tsx` strain dot · `app/stash/StashClient.tsx` strain badge · `components/RecentlyViewedAutoStrip.tsx` dot · `components/RecentlyViewedStrip.tsx` dot. amber-100/700/200/400/800 → red-100/700/200/400/800 (same shade levels, just hue swap). Indica + Hybrid colors unchanged — already correct per convention. Mirror on seattle-cannabis-web v4.515. tsc clean.
// 3.685 — Mailto subject prefill sweep — homepage contact section + `/about`. Continues v3.595 + v3.635 across the remaining customer-facing email touchpoints. Homepage's "phone | email" pair below the hero gets `?subject=Question%20from%20greenlifecannabis.com`; `/about` page's contact card gets the same. Both subjects intentionally generic — no surface-specific routing hint, so the receiving inbox can categorize freely. Two single-line edits per repo. Mirror on seattle-cannabis-web v4.485 (+1 extra: `/community` past-staff signup gets "Past staff — alumni signup" subject for routing). tsc clean.
// 3.635 — Mailto subject prefill on `/apply/thanks` + `/vendor-access/thanks`. Pattern continuation from v3.595 `/contact`. Each thank-you page's "Questions in the meantime? Email <addr>" link now opens with a contextual subject ("Job application — follow up" / "Vendor access — follow up") so the receiving inbox can route immediately. Hosts that don't honor `?subject=` still get the unprefilled `mailto:`. Two single-line edits per repo. Mirror on seattle-cannabis-web v4.475. tsc clean.
// 3.605 — Loyalty card tier display on `/account`. Customer's loyalty card now shows their relationship tier (Visitor → Regular → Local → Family) + a progress bar with `$X to {NextTier}` hint. Pulls lifetime post-tax spend from transactions (mirrors inventoryapp's tier math). New `lib/loyalty-tiers.ts` (mirror of inventoryapp `lib/loyalty.ts` minus styling). `LoyaltySnapshot.lifetimeSpent` added; both `getLoyaltyForPortalUser` + `getLoyaltyByClerkId` now SUM transactions. Skipped at top tier (shows "Top tier — thank you 🌿") and when lifetimeSpent=0 (the existing first-dollar copy keeps the floor). Mirror on seattle-cannabis-web v4.445. tsc clean.
// 3.595 — `/contact` mailto subject prefill. Bare `mailto:${STORE.email}` opened a blank email; now prefills `?subject=Question%20from%20greenlifecannabis.com` so the team can triage incoming email at a glance ("Order question" vs "Vendor pitch" vs spam) without opening every message. Single-line ergonomic improvement on the customer side. Hosts that don't honor `?subject=` ignore the param — no breakage. NOT included: hint copy steering customers from email → phone (Doug 2026-05-05: "email is fine no need to hint to call"); see `feedback_dont_steer_email_to_phone.md`. Mirror on seattle-cannabis-web v4.435. tsc clean.
// 3.585 — `/not-found.tsx` now closure-aware. Parity with the rest of the customer-facing surfaces (`/`, `/menu`, `/order`, `/visit` — all closure-aware since v3.230–v3.250). Pre-fix the 404's "Wenatchee Cannabis is open now" chip used `isOpenNow()` only, which checks configured weekly hours but ignores any emergency closure flipped at `/admin/hours-override`. Customer landing on a stale URL on a closure day saw "open now" and could drive over to a closed store. Post-fix: `await fetchClosureStatus()` + `const open = isOpenNow() && !closure.isClosed` matches the homepage pattern. Helper has 5s AbortController + graceful-degrades to `{isClosed:false}` on error, so a flaky endpoint can't break the 404 render. Single-file ship per repo. Mirror on seattle-cannabis-web v4.425. tsc clean.
// 3.575 — Brand-name cleanup extends to vendor-ad chips (`<VendorAdSlot>`). Companion to v3.555 lib-boundary cleaner. `getActiveVendorAds()` was returning raw `v.name` as `vendorName` and `VendorAdSlot.tsx` rendered it in the small "From {vendor}" chip below each ad — same legal-entity-suffix problem as the carousel ("Featured partner: Alpha Crux, llc"). Now wraps the SQL-returned `r.vendor_name` with `cleanBrandName()` (preserving null when null) so the chip reads "Alpha Crux" instead. Single-line change at the row mapping site. Mirror on seattle-cannabis-web v4.415. tsc clean.
// 3.565 — Customer-facing substitution display on /account/orders + /order/confirmation/[id]. When inventoryapp's POS substitutes an OOS item (per online_orders.substitutions JSONB), the customer's order pages now show a 🔄 "Substitution made by staff" panel listing each {original} → {sub} pair. Closes the gap where the customer was told via SMS/email but couldn't see the swap on the page. portal.ts: OnlineOrder type gains `substitutions: OrderSubstitution[]`, getOrders/getOrder both SELECT o.substitutions, parseSubstitutions defensive parser filters malformed JSONB rows. Mirror on seattle-cannabis-web v4.405. tsc clean.
// 3.555 — Brand-name cleanup at the lib boundary. Companion to v3.485 logo-filter. Even with the carousel filter, vendor names like "Alpha Crux, llc" and "Northwest Cannabis Solutions LLC" still leak into customer-visible surfaces (`/brands/[slug]` page H1, brand-deal callouts, future brand-attribution text). New `lib/clean-brand-name.ts` exports `cleanBrandName(raw)` which strips trailing legal-entity suffixes (`, LLC` / ` LLC` / ` Inc` / ` Corp` / ` Co` / ` Ltd` / ` PLLC` and dotted variants) only when anchored to end-of-string. Conservative: doesn't touch numeric prefixes ("1555 Industrial Labs"), doesn't touch ` - <text>` patterns (some legit brand names use dashes), doesn't strip mid-string LLC ("Joe's LLC Cannabis" stays intact). Applied at `lib/db.ts` `getActiveBrands()` + `getBrandBySlug()` row mappings — single point of truth so every consumer of `VendorBrand.name` gets the cleaned value automatically. Slug derivation still uses canonical `v.name` so URLs are stable. Mirror on seattle-cannabis-web v4.395. tsc clean.
// 3.495 — /alumni knock-form: empty-secret error message replaced. Was "Try again." — useless for someone who'd typed nothing yet. Now: "Type your secret first — anything you remember from your time on the floor." which (a) tells the user what to do and (b) matches the alumni-page warm voice.
// 3.485 — Top Brands carousel filters to logo'd brands. Pre-fix the homepage "Washington's finest producers / Top Brands" section sliced the first 10 alphabetical brands from `getActiveBrands()`, surfacing license-shaped vendor records ("1555 Industrial L...", "AG GROW - 4125...", "Alpha Crux, llc") rendered with single-letter initial placeholders — visually a wall of "A"/"B" cards with zero actual logos, the opposite of the section heading's promise. Post-fix: filter `b.logoUrl != null && b.logoUrl.trim().length > 0` BEFORE the .slice(0, 10) so only brands with real uploaded logos are eligible. Existing `featuredBrands.length > 0` guard below already hides the whole section when the filter returns empty (no awkward 1-card-row state). Initials fallback in the JSX stays as defense-in-depth for the rare case a brand's logoUrl returns 404 at render. Mirror on seattle-cannabis-web v4.365. Single-file ship. tsc clean.
// 3.475 — Order-status mapping fix. Inventoryapp's POS PATCH writes `in_progress` and `fulfilled` to `online_orders.status` (per `Inventory App/src/app/api/pos/online-orders/[id]/route.ts`), but the public site's `OnlineOrder["status"]` type and UI label maps use `preparing` and `picked_up`. Pre-fix: the lib/portal.ts read paths cast the raw DB string to the type without value transformation, so `STATUS_LABEL[order.status]` resolved to `undefined` for those two states — customer's `/account/orders` row + `/order/confirmation/[id]` timeline rendered blank when a budtender hit Start Order ("in_progress") or marked an order picked up ("fulfilled"). Post-fix: new `normalizeOrderStatus()` helper maps `in_progress` → `preparing`, `fulfilled` → `picked_up`, passes other valid statuses through unchanged, falls back to `pending` for unknown raws. Applied in both `getOrder()` (confirmation page) and `getOrders()` (history page) return mappings. Mirror on seattle-cannabis-web v4.355. tsc clean.
// 3.465 — /account/profile: Heroes Discount cohort select added alongside No Substitutions. Customer can now set their heroes self-attest type from the main profile page (Active Military / Veteran / First Responder / Healthcare / K-12 Teacher). Server validates against allowlist; writes to customers.heroes_self_attest_type via updateHeroesAttest(). Complement to the existing /account/heroes dedicated page and /account hub card. Mirror on seattle-cannabis-web v4.345.
// 3.445 — AgeGate: embed WAC 314-55-082 statutory health warnings (6 bullet warnings) in scrollable panel within the age-verification modal. Single "Yes, I'm 21+" confirm covers both age verification and health warning acknowledgment. 30-day localStorage/cookie TTL unchanged. Mirror on seattle-cannabis-web v4.315. tsc clean.
// 3.435 — Heroes self-attest Phase 3b: customers can now register their heroes cohort from the public-site account hub. New: /account/heroes page (Server Component + HeroesForm client component), /api/heroes POST route, portal.ts updateHeroesAttest() mirrors to customers.heroes_self_attest_type via email match (no new migration — column already exists from inventoryapp mig 0072). PortalUser type gains heroesSelfAttestType; SELECT query LEFT JOINs LATERAL to customers to surface current value. Account hub (/account) shows a "Heroes Discount" card with current cohort label or default promo copy. Mirror on seattle-cannabis-web v4.305. tsc clean.
// 3.425 — Loyalty Phase 2: tiered-discount picker on /order checkout. When feature flag `loyalty_tiered_redemption` is ON and the signed-in customer has enough points, a tier picker appears in the cart drawer showing all eligible tiers (5/10/20/25/30% off at 50/100/200/250/300 or 400 pts). Selecting a tier updates the total in real-time; points are deducted atomically at order submission via UPDATE ... WHERE loyalty_points >= X. New: lib/loyalty-redemption.ts (pure tier math, no server-only import), getLoyaltyByClerkId() in portal.ts, placeOrder() 5th param loyaltyTierPointCost, online_orders loyalty_redemption + loyalty_tier_point_cost columns (migration 0179 already applied). Mirror on seattle-cannabis-web v4.295. tsc clean.
// 3.415 — P4 pickup flow: when a customer saves their "No Substitutions" preference in /account/profile, portal.ts now mirrors it to the linked customers.no_substitute_pref row so the POS substitute route honors the preference end-to-end. lib/portal.ts updatePortalUser 1-query addition. tsc clean.
// 3.405 — `<og-image>` straight-quote → curly-apostrophe (U+2019) fix on 3 files: `app/opengraph-image.tsx` (\"Wenatchee's\" → \"Wenatchee’s\"), `app/brands/opengraph-image.tsx` (\"Washington's\" → \"Washington’s\"), `app/deals/opengraph-image.tsx` (\"Today's Deals\" → \"Today’s Deals\"). Closes the last 3 lint errors that were intentionally skipped earlier this session because satori-rendered files don't decode `&rsquo;` HTML entities. The Unicode curly apostrophe IS a literal char satori reads correctly + isn't flagged by `react/no-unescaped-entities`. Lint NOW fully clean: 0 errors, 0 warnings (matches seattle-cannabis-web v4.275 pristine state). Customer-visible text is even slightly upgraded — typographic curly apostrophes look better in OG-card preview imagery (Twitter cards, Facebook embeds) than straight-quote ASCII. tsc clean.
// 3.395 — Lint sweep finishing pass: 4 files / 5 errors silenced. `DealCountdown.tsx` line 31 (`react-hooks/set-state-in-effect`) — hydration-safe ticker reconciles SSR-initial to client-time on mount before 60s interval. `PaginatedProductsGrid.tsx` line 96 (`react-hooks/set-state-in-effect`) — canonical "reset child pagination on filter prop change" pattern. `OrderMenu.tsx` lines 1388/1392 (2× `react-hooks/purity`) — refactored to single IIFE with one centralized disable + `nowMs`/`ageMs`/`days` hoisted; preserves behavior (outer-expression guards still short-circuit). `MenuFallback.tsx` line 85 (`react-hooks/purity`) — only renders post-watchdog with stable `featuredDeal`. Lint count: 8 → 3 (the 3 remaining are intentional satori OG-image apostrophes). tsc clean.
// 3.385 — `components/AnnouncementBar.tsx` — silence `react-hooks/purity` on the `urgentDeal` IIFE's `Date.now()` (line 27). Server Component is rendered per-request (parent pages are dynamic via `await getActiveDeals()`), so the timestamp drives "ends today/tomorrow" math correctly — false-positive on a Server Component. Inline `eslint-disable-next-line react-hooks/purity` with a why-comment so the next reader doesn't strip it. Lint sweep continues. tsc clean.
// 3.380 — 2-file dead-disable cleanup: `MobileStickyCta.tsx` (line 98 `react-hooks/set-state-in-effect` inside `.then(...)` async callback — rule doesn't fire on async setState) + `RecentlyViewedAutoStrip.tsx` (2 of 3 disables: the `.then()` + `.catch()` async setState branches were dead, kept the synchronous `setProducts([])` early-return disable since the rule does fire there). Verified via `pnpm lint` — no new errors introduced. Sister to v3.345 cleanup philosophy: trim disables that no longer guard a real rule firing so future real lint warnings don't get drowned in stale-noise. tsc clean.
// 3.365 — `app/page.tsx` — drop unused `eslint-disable-next-line react-hooks/purity` on `Date.now()` deal-countdown calc. The rule wasn't actually firing (force-dynamic page lets Date.now() through), so the directive was dead. Lint cleanup. tsc clean.
// 3.360 — 3 more unused-var/import cleanups: `bondi-farms.tsx` (unused `Image`) + `avitas.tsx` (unused `BRAND_AMBER_LIGHT` const) + `PaginatedProductsGrid.tsx` (dropped 17-line dead `buckets` useMemo — category-grouping computation that nothing rendered). tsc clean.
// 3.355 — 2 unused-import lint cleanups: `app/account/profile/page.tsx` (unused `STORE`) + `app/brands/[slug]/_brands/2k-gardens.tsx` (unused `Link`). Both leftover from prior refactors. tsc clean.
// 3.350 — `app/alumni/page.tsx` — `<a href="/">` → `<Link>` for the customer-facing "Back to the shop" CTA. Real perf fix: `<a>` does a full page reload while `<Link>` does client-side nav (preserves cart state, reuses cached data, faster). Caught by `@next/next/no-html-link-for-pages` lint. tsc clean.
// 3.345 — `components/CartResumeBanner.tsx` — add 2 missing `eslint-disable-next-line react-hooks/rules-of-hooks` directives on `useEffect` calls. Component has `if (!PUBLIC_ORDER_ROUTE_LIVE) return null` early-return at line 69; the constant is hardcoded `false` so hooks below never execute. Author already disabled `usePathname`/`useSyncExternalStore`/`useState` calls but missed the 2 `useEffect`. Lint silence; runtime unchanged. tsc clean.
// 3.340 — `components/LoyaltyArc.tsx` JSX apostrophe fix (`We're` → `We&rsquo;re`). Caught by `pnpm lint` `react/no-unescaped-entities` on the customer-visible homepage loyalty section. Tiny 1-character JSX hygiene fix; renders identically but stops the lint error so future real-bug warnings don't get drowned in noise. Sister fix on seattle-cannabis-web v4.240. Skipped the 3 opengraph-image.tsx files since those are satori-rendered (HTML entities don't auto-decode). tsc clean.
// 3.335 — `lib/order-confirmation-email.ts` + `lib/welcome-email.ts` opt-out mailto switched from hardcoded `info@greenlifecannabis.com` to `RESEND_REPLY_TO ?? STORE.email`. Pre-fix the customer-facing footer line ("To stop future marketing emails, reply STOP or email info@greenlifecannabis.com") sent unsubscribers to an unmonitored inbox per `project_info_email_unmonitored` memory — same class of bug as inventoryapp v56.245 `/api/applications` reply-to. Post-fix: prefers `RESEND_REPLY_TO` env (set to monitored `buyer@greenlifecannabis.com` v3.325), falls through to STORE.email as last resort. Same env var that drives the Resend reply-to header so monitoring fate is now consistent across header + in-body opt-out paths. 2 files / 6 lines changed (3 hardcoded refs per file: HTML mailto + plain-text body + comment block documenting the WHY). tsc clean. Customer-facing fix — applicants/customers replying to opt out actually reach a monitored inbox now.
// 3.330 — `lib/sms.ts` upgraded to inventoryapp's `normalizeToE164` boundary pattern (companion to inventoryapp v50.345). Pre-fix: `sendSms()` passed raw `to` straight to Twilio without normalization; the existing `normalizePhone` helper was simplistic (only handled `+`-prefix and naive 10-digit, broke on formatted `(509) 555-0100` and 11-digit `1XXX...`). Post-fix: new `normalizeToE164(input)` handles raw 10-digit US, formatted US, already-E.164, 11-digit `1XXX`, 11+-digit international, and empty/short input (returns unchanged so Twilio rejection is the cleaner failure path). `sendSms()` now calls it at the boundary so callers don't have to remember. `normalizePhone` kept as a back-compat alias (E.164 round-trips unchanged, so existing inline calls in `/api/orders` keep working). Same surgery on seattle-cannabis-web v4.230. Single-file +35 LOC. tsc clean. Closes the SMS-helper drift between the inventoryapp + the two public sites flagged by `feedback_sms_e164_normalize_at_boundary`.
// 3.325 — `lib/email.ts` honors `RESEND_REPLY_TO` env var (default reply-to override). Pre-fix: customer replies to outbound mail defaulted to the From address — fine when From is monitored, but Wenatchee's `info@greenlifecannabis.com` From is NOT actively monitored (per memory `project_info_email_unmonitored`), so replies vanished. Post-fix: when `RESEND_REPLY_TO` env var is set, sendEmail() routes replies there instead. Per-call `replyTo` arg still wins; env-var default is the fallback. Wired live: `buyer@greenlifecannabis.com` set on this project (all 3 envs) since that mailbox IS actively monitored. Seattle unchanged — its From (`rainier@seattlecannabis.co`) is monitored so RESEND_REPLY_TO stays unset, but the helper now supports the env var symmetrically across both repos. Mirror on seattle-cannabis-web v4.225 (helper-only; no env var set).
// 3.320 — `/menu` server-side Dutchie prewarm. New `prewarmDutchieMenu()` async helper inside `app/menu/page.tsx` does a fire-alongside `fetch("https://api.iheartjane.com/api/v1/stores/5294/menu_products?per_page=1")` at SSR time, BEFORE the HTML response reaches the browser. Boost (which runs `afterInteractive` in `JaneMenu.tsx`) then queries the same URL ~200ms after page paint and hits Jane's now-warm edge cache — Dutchie cold-start time is amortized away from the customer's first paint. AbortSignal 1.5s timeout caps TTFB impact when Jane is unreachable; failure path silently swallowed (helper returns void). Closes the customer-reported "menu error coming up first pass" pattern (MenuFallback's amber 6s watchdog was firing on cold-Dutchie loads even though Boost was just-about to succeed). See MENU_LOG.md + MenuFallback.tsx FALLBACK_AFTER_MS for the dodged threshold. Mirror on seattle-cannabis-web v4.220.
// 3.315 — `/api/health` exposes `emailConfigured: boolean` for one-curl Resend wire-up verification. After adding `RESEND_API_KEY` env var to a Vercel project, this flag flips `true` on the next deploy. Boolean only — never the key value. Companion to seattle-cannabis-web v4.215 (same single-line addition, mirrors the email helper at `lib/email.ts`).
// 3.311 — vendor-ads `daily_impression_cap` render-side enforcement (companion to inventoryapp v49.705 + migration 0158). `getActiveVendorAds()` now (1) excludes any ad whose TODAY's count has already hit cap via WHERE branch — `last_impression_day IS DISTINCT FROM today OR impressions_today < cap`, (2) atomic post-SELECT UPDATE increments `impressions_today` (or resets to 1 if day rolled over). Day boundary computed in `America/Los_Angeles` so rollover lines up with Kat's calendar. Lazy-reset semantics — no daily cron required. UPDATE failure swallowed (render quality > telemetry). Mirror on seattle-cannabis-web v4.211.
// 3.305 — `/api/health` redacts Neon endpoint ID from `db.host`. Pre-fix exposed `ep-divine-voice-ant9tbpu-pooler.c-6.us-east-1.aws.neon.tech` to anonymous health-check callers — the leading label uniquely identifies the Neon project. Now redacts to `***.c-6.us-east-1.aws.neon.tech` — keeps cluster/region/provider for ops "is this Neon? right region?" debug, drops project-uniqueness leak. Same fix on seattle-cannabis-web v4.200 + inventoryapp v49.045. Auth'd ops reading raw env var still see full hostname.
// 3.300 — Stale `/brands` index reference cleaned up in dev landing page (`app/dev/page.tsx`). Row was pointing at the deleted index (308's to /menu via v3.290 middleware) with a misleading "Per-vendor product listings" blurb. Repurposed to point at a sample boutique override page (`/brands/nwcs`) so Doug + devs previewing the dev menu can see the live `/brands/[slug]` template. Greenlife-only — Seattle has no `/dev` route. Single-file ship, single-line + comment block.
// 3.295 — VendorAdSlot wired to 4 remaining placement slots: homepage_top (above hero), homepage_under_brands (below brands carousel), menu_sidebar (above iHeartJane Boost embed on /menu), brand_page_top (top of /brands/[slug] generic template). All slots silent until admin curates active ads at inventoryapp /admin/marketing/vendor-ads. Now 5 of 5 schema-enum slots are mounted. Mirror on seattle-cannabis-web v4.195.
// 3.290 — `/brands` redirect FINAL FIX in `proxy.ts` middleware. v3.265's page-level approach (`permanentRedirect()` + `dynamic = "force-dynamic"`) deployed but did NOT produce a real HTTP 308 — Next 16 served HTTP 200 with homepage HTML body even though page was rendered dynamically (no `x-vercel-cache: HIT`). Middleware-level intercept runs BEFORE Next's render pipeline; response is a guaranteed real HTTP 308 with `location: /menu`. Page-level fallback in `app/brands/page.tsx` remains as defense-in-depth. Closes the `🟡 /brands redirect caveat` flag in LIVE.md. Mirror on seattle-cannabis-web v4.190.
// 3.281 — `proxy.ts` `ALWAYS_CANONICAL_HOSTS` belt-and-suspenders set added (parity with seattle-cannabis-web). Defends against `NEXT_PUBLIC_CANONICAL_HOST` env-var misconfiguration — if anyone ever sets it to a stale value or per-deployment Vercel URL, `isCanonicalOrLocal()` still treats `www.greenlifecannabis.com` as canonical and won't redirect customers AWAY from it. Same defense class as the inventoryapp cross-store warp hardening (v45.205) — env-var misconfig shouldn't be able to break SSO/CORS pinning. Mirror of Seattle's existing pattern. Single-line addition + comment block. Single-file. tsc clean.
// 3.270 — `/brands` redirect moved to proxy.ts middleware (FIRST attempt — see v3.290 for the actual ship). Note: this entry never landed in production with the middleware change because the proxy.ts edit didn't get committed in the same push. Kept here as historical narrative.
// 3.265 — `/brands` redirect SEO fix. Was returning HTTP 200 + a Next.js Loading-then-`router.push("/menu")` static payload (Next 16 captures `redirect()` during prerender as static HTML when there's no `dynamic = "force-dynamic"` directive on the page). Crawlers + uptime checks + curl saw 200 + empty body, not a redirect. Now: `export const dynamic = "force-dynamic"` forces per-request render, and `redirect` swapped for `permanentRedirect` so the response is a real HTTP 308 → /menu (matches the page comment's stated intent + the LIVE.md follow-up note). SEO impact: search engines + crawlers + monitors now see a proper permanent redirect; link equity from any inbound `/brands` references flows correctly to /menu. Mirror on seattle-cannabis-web v4.175.
// 3.260 — Homepage 🆕 Just In section. New `getJustInProducts(12)` lib fn pulls products with `inventory_snapshots.first_seen ≤ 7 days ago`, in stock now, with image, brand-with-recent-sales gate (same anti-leak as getMenuProducts). Renders above the (still-disabled-pending-/order-ship) Today's Picks block as a fresh 4-column grid with a "🆕 New" pill in the corner of each card. CTA links to /menu (iHeartJane Boost) — distinct from the in-dev /order tree. Distinct from curated /admin/marketing/featured (curated = hot picks, this = what's new). Doug 2026-05-04 "featured new products" — curated answers "featured", this answers "new". Mirror on seattle-cannabis-web v4.170.
// 3.255 — `getFeaturedProducts()` reads curated mode first. When admin (Kat/Doug) flips ON `is_featured` for any active product at inventoryapp /admin/marketing/featured (migration 0154), those products win the homepage carousel — sorted by `featured_priority DESC NULLS LAST, name ASC`. Falls back to the existing recent-`updated_at`-on-brands-with-sales auto-mode when zero curated. Companion to inventoryapp v44.x ship that landed migration 0154 + the admin curation surface. Mirror on seattle-cannabis-web v4.165.
// 3.250 — Homepage closure-aware. Adds `fetchClosureStatus()` to the page-level `Promise.all` and threads `closure.isClosed` into the existing `const open = isOpenNow()` so all 3 hero/strip/pre-footer "Open Now / Closed" indicators flip to "Closed" when a manager has flipped the emergency-closure override — matching the reality of the store, not just configured weekly hours. Also renders `<ClosureBanner>` at the very top of the page (above the hero) inside an amber strip for explicit reason context. Closure-aware customer surfaces now: `/` (v3.250) + `/menu` (v3.240) + `/order` (v3.230) + `/visit` (v3.245). Mirror on seattle-cannabis-web v4.160.
// 3.245 — `/visit` closure banner. Extends v3.240 to the third high-traffic customer entry point: the visit-info page (hours + directions + parking) where pre-drive customers land. Server Component made async to call `fetchClosureStatus()` server-side; banner renders above the hero when closed (consistent with /menu placement). Page already has `revalidate = 300` 5-min ISR so the closure-status fetch happens at most once per 5min per region. Closure-aware customer surfaces now: /menu (v3.240) + /order (v3.230) + /visit (v3.245). Mirror on seattle-cannabis-web v4.155.
// 3.240 — `/menu` server-rendered closure banner. Extends v3.230's `/order` banner to the higher-traffic `/menu` (iHeartJane Boost embed) entry point. New `<ClosureBanner>` component (presentational, used by both `/menu` server-side + `/order` client-side via prop). `/menu` page.tsx now does `Promise.all([getActiveDeals, fetchClosureStatus])` server-side; banner renders above the heading + JaneMenu when closed. ISR 60s on the page bounds the fetch frequency. Same graceful-degrade behavior — endpoint unreachable = banner doesn't render. Mirror on seattle-cannabis-web v4.150.
// 3.235 — `/brands` index deletion code lands (v3.225 changelog described this; that entry shipped via the closure-banner agent's bundle but the code edits were still uncommitted in working tree). This commit lands the actual file deletions + nav-strip + breadcrumb edits.
// 3.230 — `/order` block-on-closure banner. Fetches inventoryapp `/api/public/closure-status` on mount + before-submit re-check inside `placeOrder()`. When manager has flagged today closed via `/admin/hours-override`, surfaces an amber banner with the reason text, disables the Place Order button (label flips to "Closed today"), and the before-submit guard prevents a stale-state race. New `lib/closure-status.ts` helper wraps the fetch with a 5s AbortController timeout + always returns `{isClosed:false}` on any error path so a flaky endpoint never silently blocks ordering during normal hours. Default endpoint base = `inventoryapp-ivory.vercel.app`, overridable via `NEXT_PUBLIC_INVENTORYAPP_URL` (https-only). Closes the visibility chain queued in claude-loop-grinder Batch A items 1+2 (admin override v9.395 → public endpoint v9.745 → public-site banner now). Mirror on seattle-cannabis-web v4.140.
// 3.225 — `/brands` index page deleted (Doug + Kat call 2026-05-04). Even after the v3.181/v3.187/v3.205/v3.211 filter chain locked the data down to "products we currently carry + sold within 365 days," Kat's reasons for deletion were structural, not data-quality: (a) the page exposed our full vendor relationship list to outsiders; (b) it made daily-deal vendor concentration glanceable. Boutique `/brands/[slug]` overrides KEPT — they pull SEO traffic for "Phat Panda Wenatchee" / "Avitas WA" etc. queries and pay for themselves on direct link-sharing + deal-card click-throughs. **Touched:** index → 308 redirect to `/menu` (preserves any inbound link equity); SiteHeader nav, SiteFooter, home `Top Brands` section header (kept the section but stripped the "All N brands" + "+more" + empty-state links to the deleted index), about + visit page mesh tiles, not-found suggestion list, sitemap, llms.txt + llms-full.txt, vendor-access thanks page, blog post body. **`/brands/[slug]` template:** dropped "← All Brands" footer backlink + dropped "All Brands /" top-of-hero breadcrumb + dropped the "Brands" rung from the BreadcrumbList JSON-LD (now Home → {brand}). Per-brand override components (NWCS, Mfused, Avitas, Phat Panda, Plaid Jacket, etc.) intentionally NOT touched — those are graduated hand-authored layouts. Mirror on seattle-cannabis-web v4.135.
// 3.211 — Brand-leakage round 3 — sales-history gate extended to product surfaces (/order, /shop, /stash, home featured carousel, home category previews, brand-products grid). Round 2 (v3.205) only gated brand pages; products from leaked brands could still appear on /menu+/order+/shop because those don't go through getActiveBrands/getBrandBySlug. Now `getMenuProducts` + `getProductsByIds` + `getFeaturedProducts` (+ fallback) + `getCategoryPreviewProducts` + `getBrandProducts` all INNER JOIN `brands_with_recent_sales` (vendors with ≥1 sale_line_items.sold_at >= NOW() - INTERVAL '365 days'). Customer-facing product display surfaces are now uniformly gated. Mirror on seattle-cannabis-web v4.125.
// 3.205 — Brand-leakage round 2 — sales-history gate added to brand queries (Doug screenshot 2026-05-04: "ABS Buds" Wenatchee-era brand showing on Seattle with 13 FOG concentrate SKUs). Root cause: Seattle Neon has leaked inventory_snapshots from a seed migration; v4.107 qty>0 guard couldn't distinguish "real Seattle inventory" from "ghost inventory from a Wenatchee-seeded product." `getActiveBrands` + `getBrandBySlug` now INNER JOIN a `brands_with_recent_sales` CTE — each Neon DB only has THAT store's sales (per CLAUDE.md), so a `sale_line_items.sold_at >= NOW() - INTERVAL '365 days'` row = customer paid for it at this register. Brands without any tail sale at this store get hidden from /brands index AND 404 on direct `/brands/[slug]` visits (so the hand-authored override components for Wenatchee-only brands don't render either). Same fix on seattle-cannabis-web v4.119.
// 3.199 — `proxy.ts` /api/health exemption broadened from exact-equality to `startsWith("/api/health")` so the cheap second-bucket /api/health/ping liveness endpoint also stays reachable on apex / per-deployment Vercel URLs. Pre-fix: v3.193 fixed /api/health on apex but /api/health/ping was still 308'ing (uptime monitors that hit /ping every 30-60s for second-bucket liveness can't follow that redirect cleanly). Same fix applied to seattle-cannabis-web — covers both endpoints across both stores.
// 3.193 — `proxy.ts` /api/health exemption from the canonical-host 308 (parity with seattle-cannabis-web). Pre-fix: hitting `https://greenlifecannabis.com/api/health` (apex) or any per-deployment Vercel URL returned 308 → www, masking host-specific liveness signal — external uptime monitors, post-deploy LKG verification curls, and per-PR-deploy smoke-tests all got redirected away from the host they were probing. Now `if (!isCanonicalOrLocal && pathname !== "/api/health")` mirrors Seattle's behavior. Single line + comment update. No customer impact (customers don't hit /api/health). Curl from apex now returns 200 directly.
// 3.187 — Brand pages + featured + category previews now require current inventory (Doug bug report 2026-05-04 "showing items we hant had in a long time on both stores"). Layers on top of v3.181/v3.182 carry_status tightening: those went from `!=discontinued` to `=active` but didn't add a stock-level guard. Now `getActiveBrands` + `getBrandBySlug` + `getBrandProducts` + `getFeaturedProducts` (+ its 4-row fallback) + `getCategoryPreviewProducts` all join the canonical `latest_inv` CTE (`SELECT DISTINCT ON (product_id) ... ORDER BY product_id, captured_at DESC`) and filter `li.qty > 0`. Same pattern already in `getMenuProducts` + `getProductsByIds`. Customer no longer sees brands that haven't shipped a SKU in months, or "featured" products with empty shelves. WSLCB advertising-accuracy + customer-trust fix. Mirror on seattle-cannabis-web v4.107.
// 4.225 — **New `/blog/indica-vs-sativa-mostly-marketing` guide shipped** (stack 4 → 5). 9-min Education guide. Companion to /blog/terpenes-101 (v4.105). Topic: the indica/sativa label is a useful first filter and a misleading prediction. Walks through where the labels came from (botanical → marketing), what actually predicts experience (THC/CBD + terpenes + body chemistry), how to read a strain in 30 seconds, real-world examples (Wedding Cake/Blue Dream/Sour Diesel/Northern Lights — match-or-mismatch with their typical labels), what to ask a budtender instead of "do you have a good sativa". Compliance: explicit "nothing on this page is medical advice" + FDA disclaimer. Honest voice — calls out when marketing claims don't match chemistry. Cross-links /blog/terpenes-101.
// 4.165 — **New `/blog/edibles-dosing-honest-guide` guide shipped** (weekly-cadence demo continues, stack 3 → 4). 7-min Education guide. Customer-safety topic — leads with "5 mg, wait two hours, then decide" rule (matches Doug's `budtender-onboarding` training module). Covers WSLCB-required serving caps (10mg/serving + 100mg/package), starting doses by experience level, fast-acting drinks, what to do during an over-dose (peppercorns + CBD + time + sleep), 5 things people get wrong (high-tolerance fallacy, the 1-hour-impatience trap, empty-stomach hits harder, more≠better, 8-hour metabolism). Compliance: explicit "nothing on this page is medical advice" + FDA-not-approved + WSLCB pregnancy warning + medication-interaction caveat. Honest voice (no efficacy claims, no medical promises). Sets up the cadence — 1 quality guide written per week, building toward a Google-indexed library.
// 4.105 — **New `/blog/terpenes-101` guide shipped** ("Terpenes 101 — what makes weed smell different"). Doug 2026-05-06 ask: "lets set up a weekly guide to be written as well by an expert in the subject... awhioe we will have a stack of guides." Discovery during planning: the `/blog` infrastructure already exists — `lib/posts.ts` POSTS array + `app/blog/[slug]/page.tsx` route + "Guides" nav link in SiteHeader/SiteFooter all wired. So Q1 (where) + Q3 (how) of the spec at `/CODE/Green Life/PLAN_WEEKLY_GUIDES.md` are moot — only Q2 (who writes weekly) is open. Demo guide is 8-min Education category, WSLCB-compliant (no medical claims, "nothing on this page is medical advice" disclaimer, FDA caveat), terpene profile education with 5 named terpenes + practical reads. Stack went 2 → 3 guides. Pattern proves we can run a weekly cadence without new infra.
// 4.045 — `/order/*` → `/menu` 307 redirect added to `proxy.ts` (Doug 2026-05-06: customer hit `/order?vibe=energize&category=Flower&strain=indica` and got "That didn't load" error screen). Mirrors the same redirect already on seattle-cannabis-web (since 2026-05-04). Per the standing customer-CTAs-point-to-menu rule (memory `feedback_customer_ctas_point_to_menu_only` — "Don't reverse — cost 9hr"). 307 (NOT 308) so we can UN-do this when the native menu ships and `/order` becomes the customer surface. Whole subtree captured (incl. `/order/confirmation/<id>`) — no point sending customers to a confirmation page when the order flow itself is failing. Query params dropped because iHeartJane Boost has its own filter UI and doesn't honor `?vibe=`/`?category=`/`?strain=`. Restore: delete the block when native menu live.
// 3.182 — `/order` + `/shop` + `/stash` product filter tightened (Doug bug report 2026-05-04 "saying we have things that we dont"). `getMenuProducts` + `getProductsByIds` in `lib/db.ts` now require strict `carry_status = 'active'` (was `!= 'discontinued'`, which included `phasing_out`) AND INNER JOIN to a latest-snapshot `qty > 0` CTE (was no current-stock filter at all — only the historical 7-day `is_new` subquery had any qty filter). Pairs with v3.181 brand-page tightening: same root cause (loose filter set), different consuming surfaces. Mirrors the inventoryapp `lib/menu-server.ts` canonical pattern. WSLCB advertising-accuracy + customer-trust fix. Mirror on seattle-cannabis-web v4.102.
// 3.181 — `/brands/[slug]` + `/brands` tightened product filter (Kat bug report 2026-05-04). `getActiveBrands` + `getBrandBySlug` + `getBrandProducts` in `lib/db.ts` now require `carry_status = 'active' AND unit_price > 0` instead of the looser `carry_status != 'discontinued'`. Hides phasing-out vendors, $0-priced placeholder rows, and Wenatchee-era stale products that customers were finding on brand pages we don't actually carry (Bon Bombs since-Wes era surfaced this). Same change shipped to seattle-cannabis-web v4.101 — Seattle had it worse since their DB inherited Wenatchee-era seed brands. SQL stays one query each, no N+1 introduced.
// 3.176 — Apply form `?position=` deep-link support — when /careers links to /apply?position={id}, form fetches position from inventoryapp API, pre-selects role + shows 'Applying for: {title}' pill at top. Hidden positionId field passes the link to /api/applications. Silent fallback when fetch fails or position no longer open.
// 3.171 — Public /careers landing (Hiring Phase 5). Fetches open positions from inventoryapp /api/positions/open?store=wenatchee with 5-min ISR + 5s fetch timeout (falls back to "we keep good resumes on file" empty state on any failure). Position cards: title, store badges (handles either→both), pay-range/hours-pattern chips, safe-markdown description (paragraphs + bullets + **bold** only — no HTML pass-through, XSS-safe), "Apply for this role" CTA deep-linking /apply?position={id}. Hero leans on Wenatchee's "best staff" angle (no "locally-owned" framing per project_wenatchee_positioning_best_staff). Mirror on seattle-cannabis-web v4.91 with indigo theme + "since 2010" heritage angle.
// 3.166 — Public /vendor-access self-serve form for brand partners (PLAN_VENDOR_ASSETS_PORTAL path B). Lands at /vendor-access — collects company + contact + email + phone + brand confirmation + intent — POSTs JSON to inventoryapp /api/vendor-access — feeds existing /admin/vendor-access-requests admin queue. Indexed (canonical), thanks page noindex. Free-text only — no file upload. Mirror page on seattle-cannabis-web v4.86.
// 3.161 — /brands/[slug] generic-template renders vendor-authored brand bio + Instagram/X/Facebook handles when filled in via /vmi/profile (inventoryapp). Section sits above the order CTA, only renders when at least one field is non-null. Handles are sanitized to /^[A-Za-z0-9._-]+$/ before being concatenated into URLs (prevents query-param injection or path traversal). Per-brand override components (NWCS, Mfused, Avitas etc.) intentionally NOT touched — those are graduated, hand-authored layouts.
// 3.156 — /apply personality prompts: two optional written prompts (product-recommendation pitch + customer-recovery story) capture personality signal without the photo discrimination risk. Stored in applicants.metadata JSONB on inventoryapp side. Compliance: written-only — no photo (WA RCW 49.60 / EEOC pre-offer photo discrimination risk).
// 3.625 — /order place-order error messages reassure customer their cart is preserved on failure. Was: 'Network error. Check your connection and try again.' Now: 'Connection issue — your cart is still here. Try Place Order again.' Same for the server-error path. Mirror on seattle-cannabis-web v4.465. Reduces customer panic when a Place Order tap fails — most customers assume the cart is gone.
// 3.151 — Public /apply form: apply-to-work intake with resume upload + 3 references + 21+ confirmation. POSTs to inventoryapp /api/applications. Compliance: no photo / no SSN / no DOB.
// 4.295 — Decorative-emoji a11y sweep round 3 — 6 more icons across 5 files. Sweeps the data-driven `{m.emoji}` / `{icon}` / `{CAT_ICONS[...]}` patterns that the v4.275 + v4.285 grep missed (those targeted hardcoded glyphs first). All 6 sites have an adjacent text label that carries the meaning: (1) `app/page.tsx` mood-vibe tile `{m.emoji}` next to `{m.label}`; (2) `app/page.tsx` category nav tile `{icon}` next to `{label}`; (3) `app/order/OrderMenu.tsx` category section header `{CAT_ICONS[category]}` next to H2 `{displayCategory(category)}`; (4) `app/brands/[slug]/page.tsx` category header same pattern; (5) `app/brands/[slug]/_brands/PaginatedProductsGrid.tsx` category header same pattern; (6) `app/about/page.tsx` feature card `{icon}` next to H3 `{title}`. Six attribute-only edits. tsc clean.
// 4.285 — Decorative-emoji a11y sweep round 2 — 2 more missed icons. (1) `/learn` LearnProgress.tsx — completion-celebration card 🎓 (decorative; H3 "Cannabis 101 — graduated." carries the meaning). (2) `/visit` page.tsx — "What to bring" 4-card grid renders a dynamic `{b.emoji}` from the WHAT_TO_BRING array (decorative; H3 `{b.label}` carries the meaning). Two attribute-only edits. Continuation of v4.275 sweep. tsc clean.
// 4.275 — Decorative-emoji a11y sweep — 2 missed icons on the homepage 'How visiting works' 3-card row. The third card (⏱️ "Plan ~15 minutes") already had `aria-hidden="true"` (it was part of the v3.X a11y sweep), but the 💵 "Bring cash + ID" + 🌿 "Not sure what you want?" cards were oversights. Each H3 carries the actual meaning; screen readers should skip the decorative glyph. Same pattern as the SCC-side sweeps (v4.825 + v4.845 wrapped 🌱 / 🔍 in /rewards). Two attribute-only edits. tsc clean.
// 4.265 — Pre-Next.js legacy URL preservation (Doug 2026-05-07: "we should also make sure we did that with seattle and wenatchee if needed", mirror of GW v2.73.20). New `redirects()` block in `next.config.ts` ships 7 permanent (308) redirects mapping the WordPress-era URL set (Wayback CDX 2014–2019, "hello-world" first post 2019-11-27) onto the new Next.js routes. Same-content-different-name swaps (/about-us → /about, /about/mission → /about, /about/location → /visit). WP-nested-blog artifact (/blog/blog/:path*, /blog/category/:slug*, /blog/author/:slug*, /author/:slug*) → /blog. Known orphaned post (/amazing-cannabis-plant-grows) → /blog. None redirect /menu or /order — those stay on canonical for the iHeartJane embed model per the rule in next.config.ts. tsc clean.
export const BUILD_VERSION = "5.625";

export const BUILD_SHA = (
  process.env.VERCEL_GIT_COMMIT_SHA ??
  process.env.NEXT_PUBLIC_VERCEL_GIT_COMMIT_SHA ??
  "dev"
).slice(0, 7);
